A, B \subset \mathbb{R}
A=\left\{x \in \mathbb{R}: x \in B\left(\frac{b+a}{2},\frac{b-a}{2}\right) \right\}
B=\left\{x \in \mathbb{R}: x \in B\left(\frac{d+c}{2},\frac{d-c}{2}\right) \right\}
b < d
c<a
A \subset B
x \in A
x \in B\left(\frac{b+a}{2},\frac{b-a}{2}\right) \Leftrightarrow a \leq x \leq b \Rightarrow c<a \leq x \leq b<d \Rightarrow x \in B\left(\frac{d+c}{2},\frac{d-c}{2}\right) 
B(\frac{b+a}2,\frac{b-a}2)\subseteq B(\frac{c+d}2,\frac{d-c}2)
B(u,r)=\{x\in\mathbb R\mid |x-u|<r\}
x \in B(\frac{b+a}2,\frac{b-a}2)\\\implies |x-\frac{b+a}2|<\frac{b-a}2\\\implies a<x<b\\\implies c<x<d\\\implies |x-\frac{d+c}2|<\frac{d-c}2\\\implies x\in B(\frac{c+d}2,\frac{d-c}2).
